data.meta_description: Lady Bromet, Air Commandant, DBE, AE, WRAF, ADC was best known as Jean Conan Doyle. She was the second daughter of Sir Arthur Conan Doyle, she served for thirty years in the WRAF, where she worked in intelligence during World War II and by the time of her retirement she had attained the rank of Air Commandant, the...
